[normal]8.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Extreme Toxicity of Counterfeit Cigarettes[bold]. 
[normal]Measured levels of lead, cadmium
[normal],
[normal] and other heavy metals in c
[normal]ounterfeit tobacco products are magnitudes higher than 
[normal]found 
[normal]in their 
[normal]legal 
[normal]counterparts. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Underage Sales of Contraband Tobacco[bold].
[normal] 
[normal]Tobacco traffickers do not adhere to 
[normal]minimum sales 
[normal]age restrictions and thus increase underage smoking and addiction.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Tobacco Traffickers [bold]Fund Terrorist Organizations[bold]. Some of the greatest 
[normal]public health 
[normal]threats 
[normal]from contraband cigarette sales are 
[normal]from 
[normal]the traffickers themselves and the violent criminal organizations they fund.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]An Inquiry into the Nature, Causes and 
[normal]Impacts of Contraband Cigarettes
[normal];
[normal] 
[normal]and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Countervailing Effects of Contraband Cigarettes
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Extreme Toxicity of Counterfeit Cigarettes[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]16.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]“
[normal]it is probable that exposure of children or adults to tobacco smoke with higher particulate levels of cadmium and lead such as those found in these counterfeit cigarettes could translate to higher heavy metal blood levels.
[normal]”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]18.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]“
[normal]The main purchasers of counterfeit cigarettes are dominantly those on low incomes, either young people who then become addicted to smoking or the socially disadvantaged
[normal] for whom so many other factors impact negatively on their state of health that the addition of another factor is potentially very serious. The extent of the U.K. market share now claimed by counterfeits means that an issue once considered marginal is rapidly becoming a major problem. 
[normal]The health risks described above as well as social implications means that early awareness of these issues is important if remedial action is to have significant impact
[normal].
[normal]”
[normal] 
[normal] [Emphasis added.]
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Underage Sales of Contraband Tobacco[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]20.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] “
[normal]cheap, illicit cigarettes...constituted a substantial proportion (~43%) of all cigarettes smoked by 
[normal]Ontario high school daily smokers, and this situation may 
[normal]undermine key tobacco control policies such as accessibility restrictions 
[normal]and taxation strategies designed to reduce youth smoking.
[normal]”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]21.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The contraband market is a key tobacco supply source for underage smokers.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]21.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]An expansion of the contraband market would increase adolescent participation in the 
[normal]illegal trafficking in contraband tobacco
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]21.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Counterfeit cigarettes are often higher in nicotine than legal products. Since underage smokers disproportionately purchase more addictive counterfeit cigarette
[normal]s, an increase in 
[normal]counterfeit cigarette supplies 
[normal]c
[normal]ould 
[normal]lead to 
[normal]more adolescents who experiment with tobacco 
[normal]becoming 
[normal]regular smokers.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Tobacco Traffickers [bold]Fund Terrorist Organization[bold]s[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]23.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]“
[normal]organised crime gangs and terrorist groups turned smuggling tobacco into a multi-million pound black market business, funding prostitution
[normal] 
[normal]and drug trafficking
[normal].”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]24.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]“
[normal]significant transnational criminal organizations constitute an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States, and hereby declare a national emergency to deal with that threat.
[normal]”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]26.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]“
[normal]Yet every day, the failure to strongly combat the growing crime of contraband cigarette smuggling deprives governments of billions of dollars in tax revenues — siphoned off by terrorist and criminal organizations. ... 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]26.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Disturbingly, the financial loss and budget effect are only part of the problem. Often the state’s loss is terrorist organizations’ gain. In 2008, under my leadership, a House Homeland Security Committee investigation found a terrifying nexus between cigarette smuggling and terrorism.
[normal]”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]27.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In addition to stealing government revenues, 
[normal]tobacco 
[normal]traffickers
[normal] steal public health and safety
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]28.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Specifically evaluate the public health threat posed by contraband tobacco; and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]28.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Inform the United States Food and Drug Administration of its findings.
